{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d7aa99fd04a4bbde5c", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70f9a489afa3080ade2d"], "chapters": ["615d6ff02b295b085ab6ebf9"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "96", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "Typical growth curve in plants is:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "bRH42", "text": "Sigmoid", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "xPiWu", "text": "Linear", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "eR4De", "text": "Stair-steps shaped", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "OudoH", "text": "Parabolic", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Growth pattern of cell, organisms is uniform under favourable conditions &amp; a typical growth curve in plants is sigmoidal. Thus following phases of growth are recognized.<br /><br />(i) Lag phase: In lag period the growth is slow. It represents formative or cell division phase.<br /><br />(ii) Log phase: Also called as exponential phase. During this phase growth is maximum &amp; most rapid. It represents cell elongation phase.<br /><br />(iii) Steady or stationary phase: It represents cell maturation phase.<br /><br />Time taken in growth phases (mainly log phase) is called as grand period of growth.<br /><br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/neet/images/ci/image4-5d465e5c-6b76-49ae-b9ff-356da5423bd5.png\" style=\"max-width:100%; object-fit:contain\" />", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbS